     <header>
                <h1>Breaking Barriers, Shaping Trends</h1>
                <h2>Celebrating the Influence and Creativity of Women in Design</h2>
                    <p><span class="leader">Women play a pivotal role</span>, in enriching the field of design with diverse perspectives, creativity, and innovation. Their unique insights and talents challenge traditional norms, profoundly shaping visual communication. </p>
     </header>


  <section id="designers" class="designers">

    <article class="designer-card">
      <img src="img/friedlander.jpg" alt="Portrait of Elizabeth Friedländer">
      <h3>Elizabeth Friedländer</h3>
      <p>One of the first women to design a typeface, her work for the Bauer Type Foundry and Penguin Books exemplified precision, elegance, and resilience in the face of adversity.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="designer-card">
      <img src="img/hische.jpg" alt="Portrait of Jessica Hische">
      <h3>Jessica Hische</h3>
      <p>Illustrator and lettering artist whose typographic craft has shaped modern design across books, brands, and digital interfaces.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="designer-card">
      <img src="img/scher.jpg" alt="Portrait of Paula Scher">
      <h3>Paula Scher</h3>
      <p>A leading figure in graphic design and branding, known for bold typography and iconic visual systems for clients like MoMA and Citibank.</p>
    </article>

    <a href="april_greiman.html">
    <article class="designer-card">
      <img src="img/greiman.jpg" alt="Portrait of April Greiman">
      <h3>April Greiman</h3>
      <p>A pioneer of digital design and New Wave typography, Greiman fused technology and visual expression to redefine the graphic design landscape of the 1980s.</p>
    </article>
  </a>
  </section>

